race.comment: SALIZOU (12) is one of many first-starters and was a soft winner of her latest and the booking of Dean Yendall, who has ridden many winners around here, is a huge plus. HELLISH LEE (6) will find this a little easier than her third on debut four weeks ago, beaten 2.5 lengths at the end of 1200m at Dunkeld, and draws well. LONG REIGN (15) is a two-start maiden who returned last time and finished tenth at Kyneton over 1215m, beaten 5 lengths. Blinkers go on here, though, so with that run under the belt she can improve. TITANIC (2) has shown some ability at the jumpouts and hails from a successful family. Can make a winning start to his career.
